<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="yet-adv">yet <strong><em>adv</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /jet/    美 /jet/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-not">1.★ <strong>[用于否定句中，常置于句末以及not后] 还；尚 (没)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We haven’t finished the work yet. 
我们还没有完成这项工作。</p></div>

<p>注: 在肯定句中用still或already。  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She is still young. 
她还年轻。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He has already come back. 他已经回来了 。
</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>[用于表示肯定的疑问句] 已经：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Have you seen the film yet? 
你看过那部电影了吗？</p></div>

<h4 id="3if-whether">3.<strong>[与if, whether从句连用] 已经：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I doubt if she has written the paper yet. 
我怀疑她是否已经写了论文。</p></div>

<h4 id="4still">4.<strong>[用于肯定句中等于still，但有较强的感情色彩] 甚至；更：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I have yet more exciting news to tell you. 
我还有更令人激动的消息告诉你。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="have-yet-to">have yet to</h3>
<p>1.<strong>还没有</strong>  </p>
<h3 id="not-yet">not yet</h3>
<p>1.<strong>还没：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Are you ready? 
准备好了吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Not yet.
还没有。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>— Have you finished your first paper?
— <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (还没有). Just half of it, how about you?  （2009 陕西改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. Not yet  </p></div>